properties.Name: Trailer
properties.Description: A trailer that is used to transfer cargo.

Columns.Name: TrailerId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a trailer.

Columns.Name: TrailerModelName
Columns.Description: The name of the trailer model.

Columns.Name: NumberOfAxles
Columns.Description: The number of axles that the trailer has.

Columns.Name: NumberOfTires
Columns.Description: The number of tires or wheels that the trailer has.

Columns.Name: InternalLengthDimension
Columns.Description: The inner length dimensions of the trailer.

Columns.Name: InternalWidthDimension
Columns.Description: The inner width dimensions of the trailer.

Columns.Name: InternalHeightDimension
Columns.Description: The inner height dimensions of the trailer.

Columns.Name: ExternalLengthDimension
Columns.Description: The outside length dimensions of the trailer.

Columns.Name: ExternalWidthDimension
Columns.Description: The outside width dimensions of the trailer.

Columns.Name: ExternalHeightDimension
Columns.Description: The outside height dimensions of the trailer.

Columns.Name: LwhUnitOfMeasureId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Unit Of Measure.

Columns.Name: InternalVolume
Columns.Description: The internal volume of the trailer.

Columns.Name: TrailerCubicCapacity
Columns.Description: The carrying capacity within a trailer expressed either in cubic feet, cubic inches, cubic centimeters or cubic meters.

Columns.Name: VolumeUnitOfMeasureId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Unit Of Measure.

Columns.Name: TareWeight
Columns.Description: The actual weight of a trailer when empty, including all liners and/or fittings.

Columns.Name: MaximumAcceptableWeight
Columns.Description: The maximum weight that the trailer can hold or accommodate.

Columns.Name: WeightUnitOfMeasureId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Unit Of Measure.

Columns.Name: GrossAxleWeightRating
Columns.Description: Maximum weight an axle is rated to carry by the manufacturer. Includes both the weight of the axle and the portion of a vehicle's weight carried by the axle.

Columns.Name: MaximumLoadCapacityPounds
Columns.Description: The maximum load capacity of the trailer.

Columns.Name: ChassisWeightPounds
Columns.Description: Weight of the empty trailer, without occupants or load.

Columns.Name: TrailerMaximumCapacityWeightPounds
Columns.Description: The maximum capacity weight of the trailer.

Columns.Name: TrailerCubicCapacitySqFt
Columns.Description: The cubic capacity of the trailer.

Columns.Name: LongCombinationVehicleIndicator
Columns.Description: In general, vehicles longer than a standard doubles rig (tractor and two 28-foot semitrailers). Examples of LCVs which are permitted in some U.S. western states and eastern toll roads: Twin 48-foot trailers; triple 28-foot trailers.

Columns.Name: ContainerChassisIndicator
Columns.Description: Single-purpose semi trailer designed to carry a shipping container.

Columns.Name: LowboyTrailerIndicator
Columns.Description: Open flat-bed trailer with a deck height very low to the ground, used to haul construction equipment or bulky or heavy loads.

Columns.Name: AbsBrakesIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the trailer has ABS brakes.

Columns.Name: PintleHookRequiredIndicator
Columns.Description: Coupling device used in double trailer, triple trailer and truck-trailer combinations. It has a curved, fixed towing horn and an upper latch that opens to accept the drawbar eye of a trailer or dolly.

Columns.Name: AirRideSuspensionIndicator
Columns.Description: Suspension which supports the load on air-filled rubber bags rather than steel springs. Compressed air is supplied by the same engine-driven air compressor and reservoir tanks which provide air to the air brake system.

Columns.Name: LiftAxleIndicator
Columns.Description: Extra, unpowered axle needed only when the vehicle is loaded, allowing it to meet federal and state vehicle weight standards. The lift axle is mounted to an air spring suspension that raises the axle when it is not required.

Columns.Name: PullTrailerIndicator
Columns.Description: Short, full trailer (supported by axles front and rear) with an extended tongue.

Columns.Name: PupTrailerIndicator
Columns.Description: Short semi trailer, usually between 26 and 32 feet long, with a single axle.

Columns.Name: ReeferTrailerIndicator
Columns.Description: Refrigerated trailer with insulated walls and a self-powered refrigeration unit. Most commonly used for transporting food.

Columns.Name: RoadRailerIndicator
Columns.Description: Semi trailer specially designed to travel both on highway and on rails

Columns.Name: FixedTandemIndicator
Columns.Description: Assembly of two axles and suspension that is attached to the chassis in one place, and cannot be moved fore and aft. (see Sliding Tandem)

Columns.Name: ConvertibleTrailerIndicator
Columns.Description: convertible: a truck or trailer that can be used either as a flatbed or open top by means of removing side panels.

Columns.Name: RefrigeratedContainerIndicator
Columns.Description: Reefer / Refrigerated container.

Columns.Name: TrailerTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Trailer Type.

Columns.Name: AssetId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Asset.

Columns.Name: OwningPartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.
